  "text": "In the numerical calculations, we also compared the complexity of the signals with Approximate Entropy (ApEn) and Sample Entropy (SampEn). Our results remain in line with those previously described in the literature [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . In the analysis of signal complexity in a 250 beat window, ApEn is as effective as SampEn and both of the entropy measures lead to identical conclusions despite the values of ApEn being higher than the values of SampEn. As previously explained, this difference arises from the properties of ApEn.",
